overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. I began by conducting a
  thorough review of the existing visual design, identifying areas for
  improvement in color, typography, spacing, form elements, and overall visual
  interest. The approach involved implementing a new, calming sleep-themed color
  palette, redesigning the main form layout with subtle background elements and
  an enhanced progress indicator, and overhauling the welcome screen with
  feature cards. All UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and
  cards were polished for a cohesive look. Crucially, consistent styling was
  applied across all questionnaire sections, replacing generic gray boxes with
  themed card-like groupings. During the process, a React console error
  regarding null values in input fields was identified and fixed by ensuring
   values were converted to empty strings. The final outcome is a much
  more polished, cohesive, and thematically appropriate application.
